main event: A civilian witness in Florence, Oregon reported seeing a white or silver object shaped like a bowling pin, approximately 12-15 feet in length, that was traveling at a speed of 600-900 mph.
interesting points: The object was observed for 1-2 minutes before it disappeared in a straight southerly direction.
The witness was outside looking at the stars when he noticed the object, which was estimated to be at an altitude of 2,225 feet directly above the observer.
The object made no sound and left no trail.
The witness moved around in an effort to regain visual contact with the object, but was unable to do so.
Weather conditions were clear with no surface wind, and there was no other air traffic reported in the area at the time of the sighting.
